@jimmychin and I are so proud to share our latest film - WILD LIFE -, and Doug and Kris' story, with the world. 

Wild Life is a story of love, life long friendships, and Doug and Kris' incredible efforts to save the Chilean and Argintean wilds. It resulted in the biggest private land donation in history, creating or expanding 17 national parks over 25 years of conservation work. 

For years, I’ve wanted to make a film about a strong woman and there are few stronger and more determined than Kris. This is our shared story about protecting the environment, a woman accomplishing the impossible, and so much more. 

Kris and I will be at the Angelika this week, and if you're in NYC, please come watch this movie with us! It means the world to be able to share this with an audience.

@nyadmovie premiered in theaters last week on October 20th.  It will continue to play this week on the big screen worldwide until it debuts on @netflixfilm November 3rd. There have been many special moments especially as we’ve been working on this film for over three years and it’s our “narrative feature” (fiction) debut. With al the suffering in the world it’s been hard to find the words or motivation to share these moments as there are CRITICAL events and issues  right now both here and abroad. That said, @nyadmovie is based on the true story of Diana Nyad who woke up at 60 and realized that while the world thinks it’s done with her - she’s not done. Nyad goes on to attempt her dream swim the 110 miles from Cuba to Florida. Working with Annette Bening, Jodie Foster, Rhys Ifans, Chris Tellefsen @jakebraver @claudiomirandadop @alexandredesplatofficial @jimmychin many of whom are parents to daughters and understand the importance of this story.  It’s been a privilege working with all of you. Thank you. And the cake is the brainchild of @ccpanos 🙏♥️🙏

Excited to announce that I’ll be joining Galerie as a curator with a list of some of my own favorite films! @GalerieFilms is a film club built and curated by filmmakers with a mission of inspiring film conversation with videos, essays, and live events. Proud to be joining Mike Mills, Karyn Kusama, Ed Lachman, Taylor Russell, Ethan Hawke, Maggie Gyllenhaal and all the other incredible artists we love and admire in this community. 

I often say filmmaking is the only thing I know how to do, so here are some of the stories that have inspired my own work and shaped me as an artist throughout the years.  Please go out and watch, debate, and be wowed by these films, I hope you enjoy them as much as I do!

It's not every day that an Oscar-winning director/producer comes to class — but @BPerlmutt’s documentary filmmaking course got to experience just that when Elizabeth @ChaiVasarhelyi '00 stopped by. 🎬 

Amidst the release of her latest project @NyadMovie, Elizabeth spoke with the @princetonarts class about her movie making process, and also screened the new film at @princetongarden.

"Nyad" tells the story of @diananyad who takes on the "Mount Everest" of swims — the 110-mile trek from Cuba to Florida. The movie is Elizabeth's first narrative feature. @freesolofilm, co-produced by Jimmy Chin, earned Elizabeth a Best Documentary Feature at @theoscars in 2019.

Tap the link in bio to learn more about @ChaiVasarhelyi's visit to #PrincetonU.

What an evening. We finally finally got the opportunity to gather our Nyad family to celebrate our incomparable leading actress - the one and only Annette Bening. Thank you @telluridefilmfest and the cinema champion driving force behind the telluride film festival Julie Huntsinger for recognizing Annette’s remarkable career as an actor with the festival’s golden medallion tribute award. Jody Foster was hilarious and on point interviewing Annette in front of a rapt audience and Annette’s clip reel surveying her 30 year plus career was astonishing. From the grifters, to Mars Attack, American Beauty and beyond I am reminded moment after moment again of just how lucky we were that Annette chose to partner with us on @nyadmovie And yes @megryan was there to give Annette the award! I mean it’s not often you get a lineup of iconic power women like that! @jimmychin @juliaallyncox @diananyad @bonniestoll @megryan @emiliawickstead
